div1.p:
Q. When did you see that person again? A. I saw him about five or six minutes after - I was then at the surgeon's door; the prisoner is that man, but he had a brown coat on when I saw him - he was between two men; I do not know whether they were Policemen - I did not know he was in custody; he was quite close to me, and I said, "Good God! that is the man that struck the blow;" I did not observe whether he made any answer - he must have heard me; it was him I applied the observation to - I had not the least doubt of his being the man who struck the blow, nor have I now;
William Wilson
has pointed out to me a spot in Gray's Inn-lane - I saw the prisoner at that spot; it is the very spot where I lost him.
